title: Grateful Dead Live at The Matrix Club on 1966-12-01
description:
Set 1/Disk 1:

01. New Minglewood Blues
02. Betty and Dupree
03. Next Time You See Me
04. I Know You Rider
05. Big Boss Man
06. One Kind Favor (See That My Grave Is Kept Clean)
07. Alice D. Millionaire
08. Me and My Uncle
09. "We Can't Agree on the Words"
10. Me and My Uncle
11. Cream Puff War

Set 2/Disk 2:

01. You Don't Love Me
02. Beat It On Down the Line
03. Hurts Me Too
04. On the Road Again
05. Yonder's Wall*
06. My Own Fault*
07. Down So Long
08. Cold Rain and Snow
09. Viola Lee Blues

Set 3/Disk 3:

01. Deep Elem Blues
02. Something on YOur Mind
03. Big Boy Pete
04. Death Don't Have No Mercy
05. Lindy
06. Dancin' In The Streets
07. Me and My Uncle

reviews.review_text: hot love the old stuff. keep it coming

Duplicate This appears to be the same content as
http://www.archive.org/details/gd66-12-01.sbd.sirmick.26968.sbeok.shnf

There was no show on Dec. 4, 1966, and at the start of set 3 Jerry refers to it being the last Thursday show they're playing at the Matrix. Dec. 4 was a Sunday but Dec. 1 was a Thursday.
great fun for all Band is in good form, Lot's of communications with the audience. I was not there and I had fun listening.
1966-12-04 Gtfl Dead show Awesome show! this is my fav version of alice d. millionaire! im glad i discovered this site. im a huge fan of the early dead

12/1/66 Without The Hiss !!! I've loved this show for a long, long time but, the hiss was always a drawback.  I am very thankful to the Deadlist Project for uploading this new source since the hiss is completely gone!  The one minus from this is that the high end is absent.  But, but , but... that high end loss can easily be remedied with editing software.  Thanks again guys.  Much appreciated.

Date Wrong The site has mistakenly posted the date as 12/04 in the header but its correctly labelled 12/01.
